CNCP v1 24349
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12708: v-memo skips updates when used with v-for and within a v-if",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:26.774985+00:00",
  "text": "v-memo skips updates when used with v-for and within a v-if\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. click the button \"change show\"\r\n2. click the button \"change show\"\r\n3. click the button \"count++\"\r\n3. click the button \"count++\"\n\n### What is expected?\n\n1. the number is no longer displayed\r\n2. the number is displayed again\r\n3. the shown number is updated to 1\r\n4. the shown number is updated to 2\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n1. the number is no longer displayed\r\n2. the number is displayed again\r\n3. the shown number remains 0\r\n4. the shown number is updated to 2\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\r\n    OS: Windows 10 10.0.19045\r\n    CPU: (20) x64 12th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-12800H\r\n    Memory: 12.20 GB / 31.69 GB\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 22.4.1\r\n    npm: 9.3.1\r\n    pnpm: 8.9.0\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 131.0.6778.265\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIt seems the if the memo values are the same when the v-if is hidden and shown again, then an update to the memo values is skipped and only the second change is rendered.\r\n\r\nA plausible workaround is to use v-show instead or alternatively make sure the memo values are changed when the v-if is shown again. https://play.vuejs.org/#",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
